  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0480">
<l>iraṇṭumuta loṉpā ṉiṟuti muṉṉar</l>
<l>vaḻaṅkiyaṉ māveṉ kiḷavi tōṉṟiṉ</l>
<l>makara vaḷavoṭu nikaralu murittē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>If the word <foreign xml:lang="ta">mā</foreign> ' a measure ', generally in usage, occurs after</l>
<l>(numerals) beginning with <foreign xml:lang="ta">iraṇṭu</foreign> ' two ' (and) ending with <foreign xml:lang="ta">oṉpāṉ</foreign></l>
<l>' nine ', it is proper that [the change] is the same [as when the</l>
<l>coming word denotes] measure [and begins with] the sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">m.</foreign><note
              place="foot">e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">iraṇṭu+mā&gt;irumā ; mummā, nānmā,</foreign>
          etc.; <foreign xml:lang="ta">mā</foreign> is a square measure, denoting one twentieth of a <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">vēli.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
